cs.CV, cs.EM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with traffic load recognition using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) on a System-On-a-Programmable-Chip (SOPC) platform. This involves image analysis and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of intelligent re-training mechanism of the CNN with known environments suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of mathematical equations to quantify the suitability of different CNN models, which suggests involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of traffic load recognition suggests involvement of the electromagnetics (cs.EM) sub-category.
